Aeneas, great warrior though he is, is still more the civilizing hero, of whom Homer afforded no example. The Homeric heroes destroy cities: he founds them. His constant epithet is pius, just as it is only to his chief soe Turnus that the term violens is applied. ‘Hic psetatz's honos?’ exclaims Venus in her appeal to Jupiter. And he unrolls for her the secrets of Fate:
